Title   : Gainers & Losers: Poonawalla Fincorp, Dev Accelerator, and Biocon among 7 major movers on Thursday. Here’s why 
Source  : economictimes.indiatimes.com
Published: 2025-09-18T11:34:50
Fetched : 2025-09-18T15:09:32.745732
URL     : https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/stocks/news/gainers-losers-poonawalla-fincorp-dev-accelerator-and-biocon-among-7-major-movers-on-thursday-heres-why/slideshow/123975510.cms
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Gainers & Losers: Urban Company and Biocon among 7 major movers on Thursday. Here’s why
ThinkStock Photos
2/9
Newsmakers of D-Street
Indian benchmark indices extended their winning streak on Thursday, led by gains in IT and pharma stocks. The Nifty ended at 25,423.60, up 93.35 points or 0.37%, while the BSE Sensex closed at 83,013.96, rising 320.25 points or 0.39%. Here are seven stocks that were in focus today
iStock
3/9
Poonawalla Fincorp
Shares surged over 12% to end at Rs 502.30 on the NSE, after hitting a 52-week high of Rs 513.35. The rally came after the company completed a preferential share allotment worth nearly Rs 1,500 crore to promoter entity Rising Sun Holdings Private Limited.
ETMarkets.com
4/9
Biocon
Shares jumped 4.3% to Rs 369.40 on the NSE after subsidiary Biocon Biologics secured U.S. FDA approval for two denosumab biosimilars, along with a provisional interchangeability designation to drive broader adoption.
iStock
5/9
Urban Company
Shares extended gains on the second day of listing, closing at Rs 169.95, up 1.87% from Wednesday. The stock has now surged 65% over its issue price of Rs 103.
iStock
6/9
Deccan Gold Mines
Shares rose 11% to close at Rs 137.35 on the BSE after reports said India’s first large private gold mine in Andhra Pradesh is likely to begin full-scale production sooner than expected.
iStock
7/9
Sarda Energy
Shares fell for the third straight day, ending at Rs 568.30, down 5.65%. The stock has lost 11% over the last three sessions.
iStock
8/9
Dev Accelerator
Shares were locked in a 5% lower circuit at Rs 60.84 on the NSE, a day after debuting on the bourses. The stock has slipped back to its IPO price of Rs 61 per share.
iStock
9/9
Dreamfolks Services
Shares hit the 5% lower circuit for the second consecutive session, plunging to Rs 124.51 on the NSE. The fall followed the company’s announcement of an immediate exit from the domestic airport lounges business. (Disclaimer: Recommendations, suggestions, views and opinions given by the experts are their own. These do not represent the views of The Economic Times)

