Title   : Profit-taking likely as Nifty nears key resistance; Jio Finance, IIFL among top picks 
Source  : economictimes.indiatimes.com
Published: 2025-09-18T09:14:59
Fetched : 2025-09-18T15:13:27.719404
URL     : https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/stocks/news/profit-taking-likely-as-nifty-nears-key-resistance-jio-finance-iifl-among-top-picks/articleshow/123970815.cms
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Rahul Sharma, Market Strategist, shared his outlook, noting the sharp upward move and the importance of exercising caution as resistance levels come into play. “So, it has been quite a move for the key indices over the last couple of weeks and we have seen a good 800-point rally happening on the Nifty. Now as we close towards the 25,500 mark, the risk-reward is not favourable for fresh longs. In fact, profit booking is something that we are advising clients as we head towards this resistance zone,” he said.
According to Sharma, a short-term correction may be on the cards. “Now, a bit of a correction post hitting this resistance is something that we have as an expectation and in a dip one should look to buy possibly around the 25,200, 25,100 zone. So, as of now, if you have traded longs over the last few days this is a good time to be booking profits."
Sharma further said that post a dip the market would become attractive once again for fresh long positions.
When asked about specific stock ideas, Sharma highlighted two names that continue to show promising setups.
“One of them is Jio Finance. The stock has been consolidating in the range of 310 to 315, 316 on the upside. In fact, the stock has formed a rounding bottom on the daily charts. Now, we have seen the stock move very well over the past from this 310, 305 zone. So, from a positional perspective, we feel 330 to 340 is something which is very much on the cards. One can look to buy at these levels in the cash or even one can look to buy the ATM call options in the same. The positional view is positive for a good upside from current level, stop loss can be placed at 307 for fresh long positions,” he suggested.
Alongside Jio Finance, IIFL Finance was also on his radar. “The second stock which is looking good on the long side is IIFL. Now IIFL is also a very similar setup. The stock is consolidating near its 20-day EMA. The stock has not participated at all in this recent rally that we have seen in the market and in fact, the stock after making a base at 430 has slowly, quietly inched towards the 450 mark. So, over 450 the bias remains positive for IIFL Finance. One can look to expect a target of Rs 480 to Rs 500 on the upside, buying can be done at these levels with stop loss placed at 435,” Sharma added.
As benchmarks test key resistance levels, the focus is shifting from chasing momentum to selective stock picking. While a near-term dip could cool off overheated indices, opportunities in quality counters like Jio Finance and IIFL may provide investors with favorable entry points.
