Title   : Top gainers & losers today, 18 September: Eternal, Sun Pharma lead gains; Tata Motors, Trent decline
Source  : www.thehindubusinessline.com
Published: 2025-09-18T14:07:58
Fetched : 2025-09-18T15:20:05.641893
URL     : https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/markets/stock-markets/nse-bse-stock-market-top-gainers-top-losers-today-eternal-sunpharma-infy-hdfcbank-hcltech-18-september-2025/article70066151.ece
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Share prices of Eternal Ltd, Sun Pharmaceutical Industries Ltd, Infosys Ltd, HDFC Bank Ltd and HCL Technologies Ltd emerged as the top gainers on Thursday.
Among the laggards were Tata Motors Ltd, Trent Ltd, Bajaj Finance Ltd, UltraTech Cement Ltd, and Asian Paints Ltd.
Benchmark indices advanced for the third straight session, with the BSE Sensex closing 0.39 per cent or 320.25 points higher at 83,013.96. The NSE Nifty 50 gained 0.37 per cent or 93.35 points to settle at 25,423.60. Sentiment was buoyed by the US Federal Reserve’s 25-basis-point rate cut to 4.25 per cent — its first reduction since December.
Top gainers
Eternal led the rally, surging 2.96 per cent to ₹337.90. Sun Pharma gained 1.77 per cent to ₹1,648.90.
Infosys rose 1.13 per cent to ₹1,540.25, while HDFC Bank advanced 1.05 per cent to ₹976.55. HCLTech added 0.84 per cent, closing at ₹1,493.70.
Top losers
Tata Motors was the biggest laggard, slipping 1.13 per cent to ₹711.00. Trent fell 1.04 per cent to ₹5,144.50.
Bajaj Finance dropped 0.83 per cent to ₹998.15, UltraTech Cement declined 0.71 per cent to ₹12,625.35, while Asian Paints ended 0.63 per cent lower at ₹2,478.30.
